I'm tired of mages scaling back what they ask for.  We've done that over and over, being ever so careful of game balance, and developer feelings, and other classes toes.
<br />

<br />
To hell with it.
<br />

<br />
I want the moon.  I want to feel like I did in EQ Classic at 50th level again before Kunark was released.
<br />

<br />
I want the moon.  I want our pets to make warriors feel cheap and rangers feel threatened.
<br />

<br />
I want the moon.  I want our nukes to be firmly second-best to wizards.  I want druids to cry when they match their puny little nukes against our boomers.
<br />

<br />
I want the moon.  I want to be pure offensive power and no defense again.  I want to have the raid fall silent when I cut loose and pull the irons out of the fire, followed by some respectful "damn" and "holy shit".
<br />

