			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Farslayer77 wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Ziwox that was uncalled for read his post again .
<br />
Just a curiosity question Lenieer  how many wizards were in that dkp sample ?
<br />
Also thank you for your support as well ) </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
You are quite welcome.
<br />
Yes we have more wizards than mages, I will certainly not deny that.  And yes we also recruit more heavily on wizards than mages, I will not deny that either.
<br />
We have 15 active Wizards, and raid average attendance is around 10 to 11 per raid.  
<br />
It is no secret that Wizards are probabaly the most effective damage class for high end raids.  As long as we don't overdo it and either stay out of AE range or have proper heals, no other class can consistantly outdamage a raid wizard (rogues are pretty close but they do have a better chance of eating deaths via AE spells and rampage).
<br />
BUT this is nothing new...its been this way since the idea of "raiding" came into being.
<br />
I honestly don't think (personal feeling here) that classes should be balanced based upon solo'ing.  Yes I know I can solo amazingly well, but its not something I care about personally.  SOE is enacting changes in the game design that is making solo'ing for MOST classes almost impossible or not worth the risk vs reward.  Remember the only places kiting classes can solo are places where the mobs are A) snareable  B) do not summon C) there is room.  Those places at high levels where the exp is worth a damn are few and far between.  For higher end players HoH and Plane of Fire are probably the 2 best.  But for example on the Test server the mobs at Tables in PoF now summon.  If that goes live, then that is no longer a viable place to solo...leaving just HoH.  Remember I'm talking about viable places to solo where the exp is worth spending the time to do it (and everyone will have a different opinion here).
<br />

<br />
I am not saying that SOE changing these things is good or bad to be honest.  The game is being changed to make it harder and harder to solo for all classes.  I am not defending either point of view..those that like to solo or those that don't.  I'm only pointing out that things are changing for everyone and the ability of all classes that could at some point solo is being diminished.  If you like to solo, I feel for you...I really do...because its only going to get worse.  However I still stand by my statement that the game should not be balanced on solo ability.  If they take away ALL of my ability to solo, I would not mind all that much.
<br />

<br />
The game has to be balanced on group/raid play...and HERE is where I would very much agree with you all that Mage's need an upgrade to their pets.  I honestly do not see any reason why there cannot be some type of AA or ability that would make your pets either immune to AE mob casts or have a HUGE resistance built in to the nature of the pet.  I can't see how that would be overpowering to be honest and its something that should be fairly simple to code.  Also an increase in the mitigation against AE Rampage should be considered.  Those two problems are the biggest reasons why Mages are at a disadvantage on raids...along with the fact that many guilds frown on pets on a lot of encounters due to push, lack of control of pets, etc (don't know how you would change guild mentality on pets gang).
<br />

<br />
Just as info I sent an email to SoE yesterday basically outlining these same things in support of your efforts.  I signed it as a wizard so they would perhaps see that other classes see the need for rebalancing as well.<br />_________________<br />Lenieer
<br />
65 Wizard
<br />
Ring of Valor
<br />
Bristlebane</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
